com.senacor.portal.sc.backend.model.repository

Interface CachedEmployeeRepository

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<Employee,java.lang.Long>, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaSpecificationExecutor<Employee>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<Employee,java.lang.Long>

    public interface CachedEmployeeRepository
extends org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<Employee,java.lang.Long>, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaSpecificationExecutor<Employee>
    CRUD repository for Employee Methods in this repository are primary defined to work with active employees, as they are more frequently handled The only method which is able to handle all employees has additional javadoc

      • findAll

        @Deprecated
java.lang.Iterable<Employee> findAll()
        Deprecated. 
        Marked as deprecated, because we are working with both active and inactive employees, therefore we have to carefully decide which CRUD method should we use for certain action. Because of that, many custom methods were defined and should be used instead of fetching all employees. findAll() is no prohibited to use, only has a special mark, so user shall reconsider its usage
        Specified by:
        findAll in interface org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<Employee,java.lang.Long>
        Returns:
        all entities
